The paper focuses on the performance of neural network architectures for reinforcement learning, which is a topic that falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and neural networks (cs.NE). Additionally, the paper explores the use of these architectures in partially observable environments, which is a problem commonly studied in robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY).
